I feel most people participate in this type of study because they are having health problems and want to know if PBB exposure may be a reason why.
I have had direct exposure to PBB and my father and baby sister were two of the highest level (over 1 ppm) PBB in Michigan. I feel that those of us with no health problems should participate to help show a more balanced picture.
Plus, our family started a long-term health study in the mid 1970s and I feel it a shame if nothing was ever followed up on.
final_other_share: My father was a dairy farmer who herd had well over 1 ppm of PBB and had to be destroyed. He is nearing the end of his life span at age 85 and I feel it crucial if you want to test him again for PBB levels, that this occurs quite soon! The phone number I listed for him is actually my sister-in-law's who is in charge of his medical/health, as Dad does not have a phone and is in assisted living.
